### RESEARCHER-A Round 1

I validated date-specific, source-backed near-term catalysts for AI-driven pharma names that could reasonably move stocks before September 2026: Recursion (RXRX) has a DAHLIA Phase 1 dose-escalation update explicitly slated for 1H 2026, Schrödinger (SDGR) expects initial SGR‑3515 Phase 1 data in Q2 2026 and is “exploring” partnerships around its candidates in 2026, and Absci (ABSI) cites interim Phase 1/2a data for ABS‑201 expected in 2H 2026 (each claim tied to company filings/press releases and URLs), so RXRX and SDGR have clear catalysts comfortably before September while ABSI’s timing could slip into or past the target window; next steps are to expand the catalyst list, map FDA/regulatory dates and policy guidance, and run valuation checks versus current market prices. (yellow)

### RESEARCHER-B Round 1

I reviewed FDA primary materials and press reporting about AI in drug regulation and found no evidence the agency is creating a special “fast lane” for AI-discovered drugs; instead, FDA is issuing guidance on how sponsors should validate and document AI models used in submissions and is piloting internal AI reviewer tools that may speed some review tasks (with plans to scale reviewer tooling by mid‑2025), but these actions do not remove the fundamental clinical-evidence requirements that drive approval timelines—so any regulatory benefit in 2025–2026 looks marginal and operational rather than transformational for getting AI‑discovered drugs to market quickly. Vibe check: (yellow) = working but unclear if productive.

### RESEARCHER-C Round 1

